      "project_id": 598134326487824,
      "project_number": null,
      "project_name": "Dredging Cashman",
      "project_display_name": "Dredging Cashman",
      "project_description": "The Sparrows Point Container Terminal Dredging Project consists of the mechanical dredging, transport, and placement of approximately 3.94 million cubic yards of sediment to achieve the design depths required for the new terminal. Work includes dredging within the designated federal and non‑federal channel limits, upland and in‑water disposal operations, slag removal, and full environmental compliance. Material will be transported and placed at the Maryland Port Administration DMCF facilities (Cox Creek and/or Masonville), the High Head DMCF, and the Norfolk Ocean Disposal Site (NODS), in accordance with all permit requirements and placement plans.\nThe project is executed across three dredging seasons (Oct–Mar each year) due to environmental time‑of‑year restrictions. Work includes mobilization/demobilization of all dredging equipment, bathymetric surveying (pre‑, conditional-, and post‑dredge), recirculation and water management operations, debris handling, coordination with wharf construction activities, and all reporting required by USACE, MPA, and regulatory agencies. The Contractor is responsible for achieving Substantial Completion by February 28, 2028, and Final Completion by April 30, 2028.",
      "project_stage_name": "Course of Construction",
