      "proposed_solution": null,
      "question": "<p>Section 4 of the 90% Geotech Report calls out the Gut as an area of concern.  Please advise on mucking, backfilling, lift thickness and compaction methods of the Gut.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>REPC proposes working from west to east.  First, the area will be mucked out to the limits of the long reach excavator and the soft material will be disposed of.  Following this, fill will be placed in lifts in the mucked out area in order to work outwards towards the channel.  Lifts will be compacted with a sheeps foot roller once the grade is above water.  Once adequate grade is achieved, the process will be repeated for the next section of the gut.  Please advise if this is an acceptable backfill procedure for the Gut.</p>",
      "question_created_at": "2026-02-27T13:44:27.843602+00:00",
