      "question": "<p>Myers has identified differing conditions to the contract drawings regarding the existing 60” industrial water main within the project limits. It has been located and test pitted and it is in conflict on both sides of MH-000</p>\n<p> </p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<strong> MH-000 to MH-100:</strong><br>Field observations indicate that the existing 60” water main deviates from the alignment shown on the contract drawings. Instead of being located outside of the proposed storm drain alignment, the water main shifts to the inside (berm side) of the proposed storm system. Additionally, the existing water main is installed at approximately the same elevation as the proposed storm drain.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>This results in a direct conflict where the proposed storm drain would intersect and come into contact with the existing water main, making installation per plan infeasible without modification.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<strong> MH-200 to MH-000:</strong><br>Within this segment, the existing water main runs longitudinally within the same alignment as the proposed storm drain. This creates a continuous horizontal and vertical conflict, preventing installation of the proposed storm system as currently designed.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Given these conflicts, installation of the proposed storm drain cannot proceed as shown on the contract drawings without risk to the existing utility and/or deviation from design intent.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Proposed Consideration:</strong></p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Option A: </strong></p>\n<p>Trade Point relocate waterline as shown on plan</p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Option B: </strong></p>\n<p>On the 60-inch side, adjust tie-in on the MH-000 to avoid conflict with the existing and realign to manhole 100 as shown on the attached sketch. Invert at MH-000 is higher than shown on plan at -0.11. The diversion chamber modification will be significantly impacted and require redesign. Allan Myers has a few different options that we can discuss with Trade Point and their Engineers.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>On the 48-inch side, shift alignment 6 to 8 feet to the north to avoid conflict with the waterline. This will put the storm drain closer to the toe of berm.</p>",
      "question_created_at": "2026-04-14T19:46:25.317350+00:00",
