      "question": "<p>Per note 7 of the site preparation contract drawing. During layout and initial site <br>clearing/preparation activities, Myers has identified numerous existing structures, <br>foundations, utilities, and miscellaneous features within the Limits of Disturbance (LOD) <br>that are not depicted on the IFC Existing Conditions Plan or the Site Preparation Plan. <br>An inventory of identified features, including photographs and approximate stationing, is included with this submission. </p>\n<p><br>• Multiple pre-existing concrete structures and foundations <br>• Existing fire hydrants <br>• Observation/monitoring wells and associated water/sewer services <br>• Existing corrugated piping and outfalls <br>• Concrete pads, footers, and manhole structures <br>• Unknown utilities <br>• Potential third-party access conflicts (CCBC CDL Training Facility) </p>\n<p><br>While the Site Preparation Plan notes reference Contractor responsibility to <br>demolish/remove buildings, structures, utilities, and features necessary to facilitate <br>construction, Myers requests clarification and direction regarding the extent of this work, particularly where items are not shown on the contract drawings and/or appear to be <br>Owner-related removals.</p>",
