      "question": "<p>Please advise on the filling and compaction methods for the Southern Wharf as highlighted in the attached drawing.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>REPC proposes working from the existing land and filling towards the channel to the east.  Fill will be placed and brought up to grade above the water as crews move outward from the existing Southern Wharf.  Lifts will be compacted with a sheeps foot roller once the grade is above water.  The process will be repeated as the Southern Wharf is extended as needed toward the channel for construction.  Please advise if this is an acceptable fill procedure for the Southern Wharf.</p>",
