      "question": "<p>Problem / Question / Inquiry:<br>This RFI is being submitted for record purposes, but nearly the entire existing sheet pile wall in conflict with Bent 34 and needs to be completely removed. The existing sheet piles at Bent 34 are corroded at the waterline and we cannot pull them with standard methods from land because there is nothing to grab onto. Some of these sheets are up to 53' long. Survey shots have been taken of these, please see the screenshot attached overlaid with the proposed pile locations to confirm conflicts. A CAD File is also attached. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Contractor's Suggested Solution:<br>Alternate proposed methods include using divers to rig to pile underwater, build a platform out to the outmost sheets in an effort to get under them with the Komatsu 1250 Long Reach Excavator and worst case mobilizing in a clam shell to dig that deep, get under the sheets and pull them out. We would communicate with you any additional measures we need to take prior to utilizing them, but we request all this work to be tracked under the waterside demo allowance. Please advise if you agree, thank you.</p>",
