      "question": "<p>The scour area backfill procedures call for placing course material in the hole up to 6 inches above the water’s surface, then covering with a geofabric before placing normal slag. Note 1 on the slurry wall Langan drawings state that the bottom of slurry wall must be embedded a minimum of the 3 ft into the clay layer. So, there is the conflict of how the slurry trench will be dug if we have to penetrate geofabric and course stone all the way down to the clay layer which could be 15’ deep in that area. Please provide clarification on how Myers is to proceed. </p>",
