      "question": "<p>The contract drawings indicate a gas line located in the northwest corner of the project limits. As shown, this line appears to conflict with the proposed toe of berm, swale, and storm drain system. To date, Miss Utility has not identified or marked this gas line in the field.</p>\n<p>Please provide clarification on the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Does Tradepoint have any existing records or information regarding this gas line?</li>\n<li>Is the gas line active? If so, please provide the line size and ownership.</li>\n<li>If the line is inactive, has it been properly purged and capped/plugged?</li>\n<li>If the line is active, were the existing inverts and depths considered during the design of the proposed swale and associated improvements?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Your timely response is requested to avoid potential impacts to construction activities and project schedule.</p>",
