      "question": "<p>Problem / Question / Inquiry:<br>Pile Lines G &amp; H have pile cages that extend 36\" past the pile cutoff elevation. <br>At row G, with a 3\" pile embedment through PC3 which is 30\" thick, 9\" of the pile cage will be into the closure pour between the deck slabs. This conflicts with the lower reinforcing of the deck slabs.<br>At row H, with a 6\" pile embedment through the bottom of the LB which is 34\" thick, 8\" of the pile cage will be into the closure pour and would only have 8\" of development length into the LB Pour.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Contractor's Suggested Solution:<br>RE Pierson is suggesting that pile line G extents 2'-2\" past the pile cutoff elevation &amp; pile line H extents 2'-3\" past the pile cutoff elevation to keep the HRC555 Heads within the CMP Sleeve on their respective precast pieces to avoid any conflicts while setting the precast or placing the CIP Rebar. Please advise if that give enough development strength and if that is acceptable, thank you. A sketch can be found attached to give a visual.</p>",
      "question_created_at": "2026-04-23T19:33:31.184373+00:00",
