      "question": "<p>The current State Water Appropriation and Use Permit No. BA2025S001(01) limits water withdrawal to an average of 2,472,000 gallons per day and a maximum daily withdrawal of 5,040,000 gallons.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Based on anticipated production rates and experience from similar dredging operations, including Cape May, the current maximum daily withdrawal limit may restrict the Contractor’s ability to maintain efficient and continuous operations during peak production periods.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>While it is anticipated that the overall average daily usage will remain within the permitted limit, the Contractor expects that daily withdrawal demands may need to reach up to 15,000,000 gallons per day to support peak dredging and pumping activities.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Accordingly, the Contractor requests that the Permittee:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Review the feasibility of increasing the maximum daily withdrawal limit under the existing permit, and</li>\n<li>Initiate any necessary coordination, modification request, or application with the Maryland Department of the Environment to support an increase in the maximum daily withdrawal capacity</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Please advise how you would like to proceed and whether additional supporting information from the Contractor is required.</p>",
      "question_created_at": "2026-04-02T20:19:10.988844+00:00",
