      "question": "<p>We have identified existing drainage infrastructure within the project limits that requires clarification:</p>\n<p>At approximately STA. 19+00, there is an existing 24-inch storm drain conveying flow from the existing area across the access road into the DMCF. The invert in elevation is approximately 8.75, and the invert out is approximately 8.50. This pipe appears to be located just outside of the proposed berm footprint.<br>At approximately STA. 20+50, there is an unidentified 12-inch metal pipe not shown on the contract drawings. This pipe has an invert out elevation of approximately 7.00 and appears to be in direct conflict with the proposed berm.</p>\n<p>Additionally, both pipes are at elevations lower than the proposed swale grade in this area.</p>\n<p>Please advise on how to proceed with respect to these existing utilities, including whether relocation, modification, or design adjustments will be required to accommodate the proposed work.</p>",
