      "question": "<p>Please see the attached sheet with the revised weld plate detail.  REPC is proposing to set the weld plate flush with the bottom of the precast and install a 1 1/2\" thick grouted joint over the weld plate including 1\" past the weld plate on each side.  A recessed weld plate limits access when welding and any minor deviation within the tolerances for pile location will exacerbate this issue.  Setting the weld plate flush with the bottom of the precast will ensure good access for welding.  A grouted joint will still be installed around the pile connection and will extend an inch beyond the weld plate to ensure adequate protection for the welded connection.</p>",
      "question_created_at": "2026-03-20T16:42:30.969303+00:00",
